                  <interp inst="t18300916-283-crimeloc1438" type="placeName" value="Tottenham-court-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-283-crimeloc1438" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-283-off1436 t18300916-283-crimeloc1438"></join>. The prisoner was in their shop on the 31st of August, and a person was sent to tell an officer to stop her; I did not serve her - another person was with her; they were brought back in custody of the officer - I saw the prisoner put her hand into her bosom; I followed her into the counting-house, put my hand into her bosom, and found one piece of ribbon; there are thirty-two yards of ribbon in all.</p>


               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-283-person2349">
                  ELIZA 
                  WATTS
               <interp inst="t18300916-283-person2349" type="surname" value="WATTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-283-person2349" type="given" value="ELIZA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-283-person2349" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I serve in the shop. This woman and another came in - I attended to them - they asked for ribbons, and I showed them some: they bought a remnant, which amounted to 10d.; it was about a yard and a half - they went out of the shop; I had not suspected them, and did not know why they were brought back; I had not sold them this piece of thirty-two yards - I know the mark on it; I do not know where it was.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-283-person2350">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18300916-283-person2350" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-283-person2350" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-283-person2350" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer. I was in Tottenham-court-road, and saw the prisoner and another go into three or four different shops; I had suspicion of them, and followed about twenty yards in the rear, till they got to the prosecutors'; I waited outside, and saw the prisoner put one roll of ribbon into her bosom - while I was there a young man came out, and asked if I suspected any one; I said Yes - the women came out, and I took them into custody; I found this in the prisoner's bosom.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I never went but into two shops, one to get my bonnet, and another to have a pint of beer; I then went to buy some ribbon, and saw this on a chair - <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183009160125"></xptr>I thought some person had bought it and left it, and I took it up.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300916-283-verdict1439" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-283-verdict1439" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19. - <rs id="t18300916-283-punish1440" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-283-punish1440" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-283-defend2341 t18300916-283-punish1440"></join>
               Transported for Seven Years
            </rs>.</p>
